{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = CelebriTV | image = CelebriTV title card.jpg | caption = Title card | genre = {{plain list| * [[Talk show]] * [[Comedy]]}} | picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]]) | camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]] | runtime = 42 minutes | company = GMA Entertainment TV | director = Philip Lazaro | executive_producer = Maricar Teodoro | presenter = {{Plainlist| * [[Ai-Ai delas Alas]] * [[Joey de Leon]] * Lolit Solis}} | language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]] | country = [[Philippines]] | location = Philippines | network = [[GMA Network]] | first_aired = {{start date|2015|9|19}} | last_aired = {{end date|2016|5|21}} | num_episodes = 35 }}
'''''CelebriTV''''' is a [[Philippine television]] entertainment news and comedy talk show broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. It premiered on September 19, 2015 replacing ''[[Startalk (Philippine TV series)|Startalk]]'' and worldwide on [[GMA Pinoy TV]].<ref>http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/534211/showbiz/pep/ai-ai-delas-alas-confirms-aldub-will-be-part-of-mmff-movie-with-vic-sotto</ref><ref>http://www.lionheartv.net/2015/08/gma-celebri-tv/</ref><ref>http://www.pep.ph/news/pepalerts/read/1441109168</ref> The show concluded on May 21, 2016 with a total of 35 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[Laff, Camera, Action!]]'' in its timeslot.
