The '''National Film and Television Institute''' ('''NAFTI''') is an educational institution in [[Accra]], [[Ghana]].

==History and operations==
It was established in 1978 by the Government of [[Ghana]] as a public institution of higher education in film and television production.<ref>[http://www.nafti.edu.gh "Home page"].  National Film and Television Institute.</ref>Since its inception, the institute has offered professional and academic education in [[film studies|film]] and [[television studies|television education]], in affiliation with the [[University of Ghana]].<ref>[https://www.ug.edu.gh/content/affiliate-institutions University of Ghana list of affiliate institutions].</ref>It is a full member of the [[International Association of Film and Television Schools]] (CILECT).<ref>[http://www.cilect.org/profiles/region/ CILECT list of Full Members according to region].</ref>

It was announced in April 2016 that in the next few years, the institute will be converted into a media and creative arts university college.<ref>{{cite web| author = Staff | date = 18 April 2016 | title=NAFTI to Be Converted into University College|url=http://showbiz.peacefmonline.com/pages/movies/201604/276530.php | access-date= 8 June 2016}}</ref>

