On release, ''[[Famitsu]]'' magazine scored the Sega Saturn version of the game a 32 out of 40;<ref name=fam-sat>''Weekly Famitsu'', [http://www.famitsu.com/cominy/?m=pc&a=page_h_title&title_id=883 No. 405]</ref> they later scored it 30 out of 40.<ref>''セガサターン – ストリートファイターZERO3''. Weekly Famitsu. No.915 Pt.2. Pg.26. June 30, 2006.</ref> The PlayStation version also scored 32 out of 40 on release.<ref name=fam-ps>''Weekly Famitsu'', [http://www.famitsu.com/cominy/?m=pc&a=page_h_title&title_id=6997 No. 400]</ref> The Dreamcast version scored slightly better, receiving a 33 out of 40.<ref name=fam-dc>''ドリームキャスト – ストリートファイターZERO 3 サイキョー流道場''. Weekly Famitsu. No.915 Pt.2. Pg.36. June 30, 2006.</ref>

The ''[[Official UK PlayStation Magazine]]'' said that the game would outlast ''[[Tekken 3]]'', and stated "the only thing to tarnish this is the graphics. So if you think gameplay is more important than texture-mapped polygons, consider the score to be a ten."<ref name="OPM_PS"/>

By 2003, the Game Boy Advance version had sold over 30,000 copies.<ref name="ownt">{{cite web |url=http://www.ownt.com/qtakes/2003/gamestats/gamestats.shtm |title=All Time Top 20 Best Selling Games |accessdate=1 December 2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060221044930/http://www.ownt.com/qtakes/2003/gamestats/gamestats.shtm |archivedate=February 21, 2006 |date=21 May 2003}}</ref> Meanwhile, the original PlayStation version sold a million units as of June 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/finance/million.html |title=Platinum Titles |publisher=Capcom|accessdate=August 1, 2016}}</ref>
